Part A - 30 Marks¶

• DOMAIN: Botanical Research

• CONTEXT: University X is currently undergoing some research involving understanding the characteristics of plant and plant seedlings at various stages of growth. They already have have invested on curating sample images. They require an automation which can create a classifier capable of determining a plant's species from a photo.

• DATA DESCRIPTION: The dataset comprises of images from 12 plant species. Source: https://www.kaggle.com/c/plant-seedlings-classification/data.

• PROJECT OBJECTIVE: To create a classifier capable of determining a plant's species from a photo.

Steps and tasks: [ Total Score: 30 Marks]¶

train_data = []

        train_data.append([os.path.split('{}/{}'.format(label, file))[1], label, plant_id])

B. Create new CNN architecture to train the model. [4 Marks]

In [23]:
model_CNN = Sequential()

model_CNN.add(Conv2D(20, input_shape=(128, 128, 3), kernel_size=(3, 3), activation= 'relu'))
model_CNN.add(BatchNormalization(axis=3))

model_CNN.add(Conv2D(20, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))
model_CNN.add(Flatten())

# Add 3 Fully Connected Layer with 128 units, 64 units and 32 units and activation function as 'relu'

model_CNN.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model_CNN.add(Flatten())

model_CNN.add(Dense(64, activation = 'relu'))
model_CNN.add(Dropout(0.4))

model_CNN.add(Dense(32, activation = 'relu'))
model_CNN.add(Dropout(0.4))

#Add Dense Layer with 12 units and activation function as 'softmax'
model_CNN.add(Dense(12, activation='softmax'))
model_CNN.summary()

NN_classifier.add(Dense(128, kernel_initializer='normal',input_dim = x_train2.shape[1], activation='relu'))

# The Hidden Layers :
NN_classifier.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='normal',activation='relu'))  # sigmoid, tanh

NN_classifier.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
NN_classifier.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))

# The Output Layer :
NN_classifier.add(Dense(17, kernel_initializer='normal',activation='softmax'))  # except softmax

# Compile the network :

NN_classifier.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['acc'])
NN_classifier.summary()
